item.title: Best pc I can get for £649
item.dc:creator: @Greeny Greeny
item.description:
@Greeny wrote:

For true value for money buy the parts and build it yourself. That said, you’ll always get the computer with a monitor and peripherals as part of a bundle for what seems cheaper, but chances are the components are cheap and so are the peripherals.

Depends if you really want it to perform or not, because if you built it yourself with say Corsair/OCZ RAM, it’ll generally last longer and perform better than something you buy from PCWorld which has none-branded parts.

Are you from the UK?
